<!DOCTYPE html>  
<html>  
<head>  
                  <style>  
      /*Internal CSS using element name*/  
            body{background-color:lavender;  
             text-align: center;}  
             h2{font-style: italic;  
              font-size: 30px;  
              color: #f08080;}  
            p{font-size: 20px;}  
        /*Internal CSS using class name*/  
            .blue{color: blue;}  
            .red{color: red;}  
            .green{color: green;}  
      </style>  
    </head>  
  <body>  
   <h2>Learning HTML with internal CSS</h2>  
    <p class="blue">This is a blue color paragraph</p>  
    <p class="red">This is a red color paragraph</p>  
    <p class="green">This is a green color paragraph</p>  
  </body>  
</html> 

____________________________________________________________

Commentaire :add tag fonctionne bien
             Melange html css peu pratique puisqu'il faut changer le langage detecté en plein milieu
	     Attribut css mal detecte ==> contourné par l'usage du type

